ard hit in early February, we all got excited for the beautiful white backdrops along the lakefront.  The couple invited their labrador, Rocco, to the session and they both brought along some great props and lots of silliness! Lyuda is Russian and wanted to bring some of her favorite clothes along for the session including an authentic Russian fur hat and her best summer dress. The light was extraordinary and the snow provided a clean canvas to work from.  Afterwards, we headed to Gutheries\'s on Addison where the couple had their first date, played some games, drank some tea and ventured onto the street for some more fun. Thanks to Lyuda and Vivek for such great, winter\'s day!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8088greenex.jpg\"><img src=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8088greenex-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_8088greenex\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-716\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8108bogart.jpg\"><img src=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8108bogart-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_8108bogart\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-717\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8172fswashbrgt.jpg\"><img src=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8172fswashbrgt-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_8172fswashbrgt\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-728\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8448mandc.jpg\"><img src=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8448mandc-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_8448mandc\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-720\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8337martini.jpg\"><img src=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8337martini-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_8337martini\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-719\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8597ginger.jpg\"><img src=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8597ginger-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_8597ginger\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-721\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8685zap.jpg\"><img src=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_8685zap-333x500.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_8685zap\" width=\"333\" height=\"500\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-722\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">To see more images from this engagement session, please link to my <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/dawnephotofans\">Facebook Fan Page</a>.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">[like]</span>\r\n','Lyuda and Vivek\'s Winter E-Session.','','inherit','open','open','','715-revision-15','','','2011-03-07 08:15:45','2011-03-07 15:15:45','',715,'http://dawnephoto.com/blog/2011/03/07/715-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),(801,1,'2011-03-02 10:40:52','2011-03-02 17:40:52','<h2>Where are you located?</h2>\r\nMy business, Dawn E. Roscoe Photography, is based in Chicago, Illinois and myself along with a team of very talented photographers, will travel anywhere!\r\n<h2>Explain your photography philosophy during the wedding day.</h2>\r\nThroughout the day, we photograph and document your wedding day with an artistic photojournalism approach with an emphasis on capturing great moments. Typically, we start with pre-ceremony shots and we actually recommend a minimum of 1 hour of pre ceremony coverage. We use this time to document the location, family and friends getting ready, details, environment and anything else that will add to your wedding story.  This allows us to give you photos from the very beginning of your special day so you have a full picture of how your day started. After the preparation time, we like to do either a first meeting and head to some great location spots to start your couple portrait session along with some wedding party pictures.  If you would rather see each other for the first time at the ceremony, we usually do a short family portrait session after the ceremony and then travel to some locations.  We really believe in collaborating together to discover the best location spots around your reception and ceremony area to get some fantastic couple portraits and wedding party pics. A typical couple portrait session lasts around 2 hours which allows us about 2-3 locations.  We love this time because it allows us to have some fun and relax with the couple and wedding party while photographing in some unique locations.  Upon arrival at the reception, we can take additional couple pictures during your cocktail hour in which the second photographer will stay to document the cocktail time. Afterwards, we take photojournalistic shots during the reception to capture some fun moments before and after your dinner time.\r\n<h2>Do you always use (2) photographers for each wedding?</h2>\r\nYes!  In my experience, using two photographers for the wedding is essential to capturing every moment during the day.  With two photographers, you also receive more images from your wedding than if there was only one photographer for your special day.  My team of second photographers has extensive experience in shooting weddings and most have their own wedding web sites as well.\r\n<h2>Do you photograph formal family portraits?</h2>\r\nTypically, we spend no more than 10-15 minutes just after the ceremony and photograph immediate families on both bride’s side as well as groom’s side. In addition, we photograph quick formal groupings of the bridal parties.\r\n<h2>I have a small wedding, less than 10-15 guests. What is your minimum time requirement?</h2>\r\nWe customize our packages based on the coverage time needed.  A minimum of 6 hours is required for beginning coverage time, but 8 hours is recommended.\r\n<h2>Do you provide High Resolution files?</h2>\r\nYes, we provide high resolution JPEG images sized 8x12”, 300 dpi on a DVD with unlimited printing rights. We provide a signed release so that you may make prints on your own. All photos are edited, color and exposure corrected along with minor retouching and cropping if necessary.\r\n<h2>Will the files on the disk be marked with a logo?</h2>\r\nThere is no branding or marking on the High Resolution files.\r\n<h2>Do you shoot black and white or color or mix?</h2>\r\nWe shoot everything in color and convert images to B&amp;W during our editing process. We also use custom editing techniques for toning and special effects. Black and white images are distributed throughout the DVD which also have custom filters and techniques applied to each image.\r\n<h2>Do you provide online proofing?</h2>\r\nYes, all photos are uploaded to Pictage.com where you can view all the images and invite your family and friends to look at everything as well.  On Pictage, your family and friends can also buy prints from your wedding and specialty items including canvas prints, holiday cards and small albums.\r\n<h2>How many photos do you take?</h2>\r\nEach wedding is a completely different story! Typically, with (2) photographers you can expect a range of images from 60-100 images per hour of coverage.\r\n<h2>What are you payment requirements?</h2>\r\nWe ask for 1/3 retainer of the contracted value to save the date and the residual payment 14 days prior to the wedding.\r\n<h2>What is needed to book you?</h2>\r\nAfter a consultation, we will need your wedding coverage time, any A La Carte items you desire, and then generate a contract and send to you.  Once you approve and sign the contract, all material along with your deposit must be sent to the studio address. From receipt of the contract and deposit, your contract will be signed and sent to you for your records along with a confirmation email.  Once everything is received, your date is confirmed!\r\n<h2>What form of payment do you take?</h2>\r\nChecks or money orders.\r\n<h2>Do you have liability insurance?</h2>\r\nYes, we have business insurance for all and any emergencies.\r\n<h2>What is your turnaround time for the images after the wedding?</h2>\r\nWe always strive for the best case scenario, but our standard turnaround times vary depending on the season. We usually average 6-8 weeks for Pictage upload and 1-2 weeks after the upload, we will send you the DVD of all the high resolution images.\r\n<h2>Do you have a back-up plan just in case you are not able to do our photography after signing the contract?</h2>\r\nThree options are available for an emergency situation.  For the first option, if an emergency situation does occur and Dawn Roscoe (me) is not available to photograph your wedding, the second photographer assigned to your wedding will be the main photographer and if time permits, an additional second photographer will also be assigned. For the second option, we would send an emergency email to our network of independent wedding photographers in Chicago. Usually when emergencies do happen, we do find another wedding professional who is available to shoot the wedding. Lastly, if you are not satisfied with any of the above options, we would refund your money in full including the deposit.\r\n<h2>At the end of our contracted wedding agreement for your time, what if we wanted you to stay longer and take more pictures?  What would the hourly rate be?</h2>\r\nWe can usually stay 15-20 minutes overtime without any costs.  Over 20 minutes, the rate is $200 per hour.\r\n<h2>Do we need to feed you?</h2>\r\nYes, we do ask that you feed us during your dinner time.  After 4-5 hours of running around in intense heat, cold, rain and sometimes snow and on our feet photographing everything we see, it is our only time for a break and to get some food and hydration. Our preference is to sit away from the guests, but if you do us to sit at tables, we would be more than happy to honor your request. We usually are able to monitor dinner just in case an impromptu speech or special moments occur so that the dinner segment of your day is also documented.\r\n<h2>Our wedding ceremony start time has several hours (3 or more) until the start of the reception. Can you give us a custom quote for photography during the 2 different times of the day?</h2>\r\nOur packages are based exclusively on the number of hours contracted and are consecutive.  Hours booked are billed consecutively. Unfortunately, we are unable contract an entire day with a break in time because we bill hourly and pay our associates per hour on the job site.\r\n<h2>Do you have travel fees?</h2>\r\nTravel fees only occur 35 miles outside Chicago city limits. For weddings outside Chicago limits and within neighboring states of Wisconsin and Michigan, travel expenses would include additional mileage and possible overnight hotel rooms. For traveling elsewhere , travel expenses would include hotel rooms, airplane tickets and a small stipend for food.\r\n<h2>Are there discounts for your services?</h2>\r\nSince we base our prices on our hourly rate and pay our photographers at an hourly rate, discounts are not given. Also, in each package is the editing and post production time which takes approximately 40-50 hours after your wedding and is essential to provide you with the best images and selected images with our special effects and filters.\r\n<h2>Are there any other fees?</h2>\r\nAdditional fees include extensive retouching, cropping and special effects applied to 15 or more photos, and additional hours of coverage during the wedding day.\r\n<h2>We would like to see all the pictures that did not make the final DVD.</h2>\r\nPart of the service offered with each package is editing and post-production so you don’t have to go through each photo taken at the wedding.  All photos are not given due to a number of reasons including out of focus, over exposure, under exposure, blinking eyes, and other reasons.  My image philosophy is quality over quantity which is an important mantra for my business as well.\r\n<h2>Are albums included in your packages?</h2>\r\nAll albums are A La Carte and all packages include a $200 album credit which can be used within 6 months of your wedding date.\r\n<h2>Can we order an album after our wedding?</h2>\r\nOf course! Since all the albums are A La Carte, you can order your album at any time and you don’t have to include the album pricing in your wedding package.\r\n<h2>What albums do you offer?</h2>\r\nWe use three companies for our albums, Finao, Leather Craftsmen and Vision Art Books. Each company offers different sizes, prices, cover options and finishes which you can customize based on your wedding and your design preferences.\r\n<h2>What kind of design style do you offer?</h2>\r\nWe will design our conceptual album storybook based on a chronological layout of your wedding day, picking our favorites and giving you a few design sessions to customize the book to your liking. We will also ask you to make a list of your favorites as images for consideration in the book.\r\n<h2>Can we see a few album designs?</h2>\r\nIf you would like to purchase an album, we usually meet for a quick consultation to look over samples and decide which album company is right for you along with size and number of album pages.  After you decide on everything, we design the album based on your preferences and cover options.\r\n<h2>How do we proof the album you are designing us?</h2>\r\nWe will send you layouts via email for all the albums and after (2) rounds of changes, you sign off on the all the layouts and send the album to the company.\r\n<h2>What is your cutoff date for holiday orders?</h2>\r\nNovember 15 for the deadline to receive a final approval for printing to be back by 12/25.\r\n<h2>What is the album turnaround time?</h2>\r\n4-6 weeks from design approval.','faq','','inherit','open','open','','330-revision-18','','','2011-03-02 10:40:52','2011-03-02 17:40:52','',330,'http://dawnephoto.com/blog/2011/03/02/330-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),(642,1,'2011-01-18 21:47:04','2011-01-19 04:47:04','<h2>Wedding Packages</h2>\r\nAll wedding packages can be customized to suit your unique wedding day. Wedding coverage usually starts at 6 hours and can extend to 12 hours, if needed. All packages include a DVD of edited, high-resolution JPEG images, ready to print with unlimited printing rights.  Wedding albums are a la carte and can be purchased with your package or if you prefer, after the wedding. Packages also include travel to 30 miles outside of Chicago city limits. To give you more of an idea of pricing, below is a standard package for 2011:\r\n$3000 includes 8 hours of coverage and one 2nd photographer. You receive a DVD of your images sized at 8x12” with 300 dpi which means you can enlarge to 11x14” sizes.  All images are edited, color corrected, and have minor retouching applied. Also, I give you a Special folder of my favorite images (estimated 20-30) that have been retouched with special effects and filters. At no charge, I can apply filters up to 15 images of your choice.  Online proofing is also available for you on Pictage.com, along with print ordering for your friends and family. An Engagement session or After The Day session is also included in this package along with a $200 album credit if you do decide to order an album.\r\n\r\nPlease inquire about pricing on my <a href=\"http://dawnephoto.com/contact/\"><strong>Contact</strong></a> page if you need coverage for less or more time than the standard 8 hour package. I would be happy to customize a package  based on what you need for your special day. Also, please send me information about your wedding on my <a href=\"http://dawnephoto.com/contact/\"><strong>Contact</strong></a> page, I would love to hear from you!\r\n<h2>Albums</h2>\r\nAlbum pricing varies with size, cover option, pages and images with an average range of $700-$1000 for a full wedding album. Smaller parent books and companion books are also available for $300-$500.  All books are custom-made and designed using your favorite images and design layout preferences. Album manufacturers include Finao, Leather Craftsmen, and Vision Art Books.\r\n<h2>Engagement Sessions</h2>\r\nEngagement sessions along with Day After sessions are available for more casual portraiture as an addition to your wedding prints.  Engagement sessions start at $400 for 2 hours of shooting time, unlimited locations and wardrobe changes.  If wedding packages are purchased, an Engagement Session of After The Day session is automatically included with most packages.  Engagement Sessions are always recommended, but if you decide to forego an engagement session, a credit will be added to your wedding package including an additional hour of wedding coverage or album credit.\r\n\r\n<em>Prices are subject to change without notice. One-third of your total price is required to guarantee your date and package price.</em>','investment','','inherit','open','open','','22-revision-34','','','2011-01-18 21:47:04','2011-01-19 04:47:04','',22,'http://dawnephoto.com/blog/2011/01/18/22-revision-34/',0,'revision','',0),(331,1,'2011-01-02 18:05:19','2011-01-03 01:05:19','','FAQ','','inherit','closed','open','','330-revision','','','2011-01-02 18:05:19','2011-01-03 01:05:19','',330,'http://dawnephoto.com/blog/2011/01/02/330-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(802,1,'2011-03-02 10:58:32','2011-03-02 17:58:32','<h2>Wedding Packages</h2>\r\nAll wedding packages can be customized to suit your unique wedding day. Wedding coverage usually starts at 6 hours and can extend to 12 hours, if needed. All packages include a DVD of edited, high-resolution JPEG images, ready to print with unlimited printing rights. Each DVD has a special folder of 50-100 filtered images that are designed to