sessions along with Day After sessions are available for more casual portraiture as an addition to your wedding prints.  Engagement sessions without a wedding package start at $400 for 2 hours of shooting time, unlimited locations and wardrobe changes.  If wedding packages are purchased, an Engagement Session of After The Day session is automatically included with most packages.  Engagement Sessions are always recommended, but if you decide to forego an engagement session, a credit will be added to your wedding package including an additional hour of wedding coverage or album credit.\r\n\r\n<em>Prices are subject to change without notice. One-third of your total price is required to guarantee your date and package price.</em>','pricing','','inherit','open','open','','22-revision-39','','','2011-03-21 10:21:13','2011-03-21 17:21:13','',22,'http://dawnephoto.com/blog/2011/03/21/22-revision-39/',0,'revision','',0),(495,1,'2011-01-12 18:32:27','2011-01-13 01:32:27','Thanks to Wedding Wire for featuring Maurine and Linus\'s wedding! The couple met at a nightclub in Prague while traveling in Europe for one summer. After their first meeting, they spent one month trekking through Europe and decided to spend the rest of their lives together. Linus proposed to Maurine in Sweden (where he was born and raised) and they were engaged for one year and married this past July. Maurine’s details were a unique combination of whimsy chic with touches of purple and yellow to create a bright, modern palette. The cake was made to reflect the architectural silhouette of the Willis Tower in Chicago and in the color combination of her dress and decor details. The flowers and bridesmaid bouquets were also very sculptural and artful and created color accents to highlight her vintage bridal accessories.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/template_large.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-631\" title=\"template_large\" src=\"http://dawnephoto.com/wp-con